5:
I'd be fine wherever, as long as I had
internet.
7:
Going outside's a pain. Easier and
more efficient to just order what you
need.
11:
...That's what I used to think anyway.
I've learned my lesson since then!
16:
Hanging out with my friends and
having fun? Totally worth braving
the outdoors.
19:
Can we go buy souvenirs next? I
wanna grab stuff for my coworkers
back home!
22:
Gotta say, you're more pumped up
than usual, Clarita.
26:
Hmm, well... When I was younger, I
wasn't ever able to leave the house,
so I live for every moment that I can
now.
33:
Oh, yeah, it's no big deal. I was born
an organic with a real weak body.
40:
Aside from being weaker than most
other bionics, yeah. My body's
souped up, as you can see.
43:
The whole process was more of a
big deal than it needed to be, since
my family's got appearances to
keep.
46:
Noxel doesn't like bionics, after all.
But I legitimately couldn't even walk,
so they let me have it.
52:
That's partly why I got so good at
hacking. Not much else to do when
you're sitting at home all day.
54:
...My life pretty much got turned
around when that CEO came
knocking.
58:
I thought he was some random
suspicious weirdo at first. Actually, I
still think he's a weirdo, but anyway...
61:
He burst in and started babbling
about recruiting me without
explaining what for.
63:
Didn't take much for him to hook me
in...
67:
You'll find yourself at home there—a
place to belong.
76:
After that, we speedran through a
couple hoops and boom—this cute,
cuddly super version of Clarita was
born.
80:
I feel like you're skipping over some
huge details here!
84:
Eh, don't worry about it. The point is, I
care a lot about my work and the
people there.
88:
That's enough serious talk for one
day. I say it's time to hit up some
boutiques and add some Palpebran
fashion to my wardrobe.
98:
I'll wait at the Guild while you two do
that.
103:
We could use a guy's opinion. You
don't mind, right?
107:
Love being able to buy natural
products in another world. Where to
go next...
114:
Ugh, my body feels so heavy... Hit
me out of nowhere...
117:
We've been walking so long, we
should probably take a break.
122:
You guys came at a good time!
We've got an emergency and could
use your help!
130:
Yeah, the culprit nabbed an affluent
merchant's son and is asking for a
lot of ransom money.
132:
The Guild's doing its best to track
down the culprit's location, but we
haven't made much progress since
we're trying to be subtle.
134:
We figured it'd be better to send out
small groups of non-Guild people
that we trust—
139:
Whoa, a real analog map. This
vintage stuff is pretty cool.
147:
If I were to hide, I'd pick someplace
like here or... here. Maybe here if I
was going underground.
151:
I'm not too familiar with the lay of
the land, so I can't say for sure. I also
don't have any drones at my
disposal, so I can't check.
155:
That's okay. You've given us more
than enough to work with!
159:
All right, everyone! We got an
emergency request for you all!
163:
I'm glad we got the kid back safe
and sound. Your analysis was on
point, Clarita.
167:
Eh, I didn't do much. Everyone else is
more impressive. I could never work
analog on a daily basis.
172:
With the right attitude, you probably
could. It definitely helped that Lilie's
great at getting people organized
and motivated.
176:
You've got a point there. I know I
come off as carefree, so people get
mad at me for not taking them
seriously.
185:
Yeah, but it's no big deal. I just get
the job done and prove them wrong.
188:
...Been a while since I got to enjoy an
after-work party.
191:
I've still got some paid vacation
days left, but... I think I'll stop home
for a bit and say hi to everyone.
195:
Sounds like a good idea. You haven't
been back since you left, right?
199:
...Guess it's finally time to drop the
souvenirs off.
